{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require the BBC Board to be elected by public vote rather than by appointment",
        "additional_details": "The BBC plays a central role in British public life and it is right that the Board which directs its policies should be directly democratically accountable to the electorate and licence-fee payers.",
        "background": "The BBC\u2019s Royal Charter should be amended to allow for the Board of the BBC to be democratically elected by the British people rather than by appointment. A public vote should then be held at regular intervals to fill the seats on the Board.",
